The original code has a logic error in the if statements inside each else if block where it checks for valid paths based on the current cell value and its right or below neighbor's value. The problem is that the condition `(grid[i][j+1] == 1 || grid[i][j+1] == 4 || grid[i][j+1] == 6)` can be true even if it should not be based on the grid values which results in wrong paths being added to the disjoint set.

The corrected code has only two possible directions for each street type: either right or down. The direction is decided by checking the right neighbor's value and if it does not match any of the conditions, then we check the below neighbor. This way, we are sure that the paths are correctly added to the disjoint set based on the grid values.

