# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Check for the first occurence of 'a'.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Check for the index where 'a' has occured the very first time.
2. If it is index 0, then check for the very first index at which s[i] != 'a', store this index in temp1 variable, then from temp1 check for the nearest occurence of 'a' and store in temp2 variable, and from temp1 till temp2 - 1, replace all the letters with their previous one (alphabetically).
3. If index of first occurence of 'a' is greater than 0 and store it in temp variable, then simply starting from 0 and ranging to temp - 1, replace all the letters with their previous one (alphabetically).

# Complexity
- Time complexity: **O(n)**
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
In worst case, we need to traverse the whole string.

- Space complexity: **O(1)**
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
Constant extra space.

# Code
```
