The problem was that in the DisjointSet class, the findpar function wasn't returning the correct value when it should have. In C++, the comparison operator (==) has a higher precedence than the assignment operator (=). So, when I wrote 'u == v = u', it got interpreted as '(u == v) = u'. Hence, the condition in findpar function wasn't working correctly. That is why the error was occurring.

